<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-18T10:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-18T10:36:00-05:00" n="693" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11551.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">O’Shaughnessy</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-18T09:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1914, 9 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>862. With regard to the Tampico incident, the Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs spoke of appealing to the Treaty of Guadalupe Hidalgo as a
                            solution (Article 21).</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>